- New settings inverface
- options:
    * Show appium startup command
    * write to log: -g --log
    * use local timezone for timestamps: --local-timezone
    *** send log to this webhook: --webhook
    * application path: --app
    * adress to run the server on: -address ADDRESS
    * port to run the server on: --port
    ** callback address: --callback-address
    ** calback port: --callback-port
    ** bootstrap port, to connect to on Android device: --bootstrap-port
    *** Session overrid: --session-override
    * don't reset app state between sessions: --no-reset
    * Java package to run: --app-pkg
    * activity to launch from the package: --app-activity
    * wait for activity: --app-wait-activity
    ** android coverage: --android-coverage
    ** launch AVD: --avd 
    ** AVD args: --avd-args
    * android device READY timeout: --device-ready-timeout (seconds)
    * Device name: --device-name
    ** automation name: --automation-name Appium or Selendroid
    *** Use Keystore to sign apks: --use-keystore
    *** Keystore path: --keystore-path
    *** Keystore password: --keystore-password
    *** Key alias: --key-alias
    *** Key password: --key-password
    * Command Timeout: --comand-timeout (< 2147483)
    *** Strict caps: --strict-caps
    *** Tmp dir: --tmp
    **** Intent action to start the app activity:
        --intent-action
        --intent-category
        --intent-flags
        --intent-args
    ** Don't stop app on reset: --dont-stop-app-on-reset
    ****** --debug-log-spacing (wider spaces)
    ** Don't kill adb server: --suppress-adb-kill-server
    *** Add long stack traces to log: --async-trace
- Install appium using npm
- Provide info how to install nodejs, npm.
